25/01/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Serbian Orthodox Church (SPC) Archimandrite Amfilohije Zivkovic was seriously injured in a blast at his house in the Croatian town of Pakrac on Friday (January 23rd), Serb media reported.
Police said faulty gas installation was likely to blame.
The priest was taken to a clinic in Zagreb with second and third-degree burns on over 50% of his skin, as well as broken ribs and other injuries.
(Tanjug, B92 - 24/01/09)
